headline: Is It Time To Reassess IBM (IBM) After Its Recent Share Price Pullback?
summary: If you are wondering whether International Business Machines (IBM) is still reasonably priced after its long run in tech, this article walks through what the current share price may be implying about value. IBM closed at US$292.44, with a 4.3% decline over the last 7 days and a 4.0% decline over the last 30 days, while its returns stand at 0.3% year to date, 33.5% over 1 year, 142.8% over 3 years and 216.2% over 5 years. These moves have come alongside continued attention on IBM's position...

headline: Mag 7 earnings, Fed's rate decision: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime Host Josh Lipton previews several of the biggest stories to come throughout next week, including a wide array of earnings results due out from major companies like Microsoft (MSFT), Meta Platforms (META), Apple (AAPL), Tesla (TSLA), and many more; and the Federal Reserve's latest interest rate decision followed by a press conference with chairman Jerome Powell. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
